Launch CCS Studio
Open a new CCS Project
In the new window, Set Target as C674x Floating Point DSP, and choose TMS320C6748 from the right drop down menu
Set connection as Texas Instruments XDS100v3 USB Debug Probe
Verify the connection. (YOu should see a message in the end of the log file saying "JTAG successful/successfully")
Type your Project Name
Click on Finish
Write your C code
Click on Project Tab above, and select Build Project. 
After the build is successful, Click on Run Tab and select Debug.
After the debugging is successfully initiated, click on Resume button available in the above command buttons
Find a user interface window opening somewhere (in case your code needs inputs to get to your final answer)

That's it !
